-- Bank of America in settlement talks over credit card practices-WSJ
-- By Avik Das in Bangalore
-- Thu Apr 03, 2014 04:34PM EDT
-- None



April 3 (Reuters) - Bank of America Corp <BAC.N> is in talks to may pay more than $800 million to settle allegations by the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau that it forced customers to sign up for extra credit-card products, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing people familiar with the matter.

The settlement could be announced in the coming days, the Journal said. (http://link.reuters.com/muz28v)